  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed. The package decision record records Accepted on the basis of aggregate evidence quality and expert panel consensus, though one factor — Test samples — carries an achieved level of 2 against a required level of 3. The shortfall was noted in the panel minutes and judged acceptable in light of the breadth of operating-condition coverage and the conservative uncertainty bounds applied to hemolysis predictions.",
